  "bio_raw": "Ashfaque is currently pursuing his Doctoral research in Sheffield Hallam University, UK on Thin-film solar cell technology. He has previous post-graduate research experience in Thin-film solar cell technology at Emerging Technology Research Centre (EMTERC), DMU, Leicester. He has been working in Academia for the last 6 years in different positions such as a researcher, an Instrumentation Engineer and a member of faculty. He is keen to delve into further research involving Solar cell performance optimization, as well as affordable instrumentation development for nano-electronics research. He is also keen in multidisciplinary research related to energy policy and sustainability.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Semiconductor Physics, Nanoelectronics, Instrumentation, Thin-film Photovoltaic, Mechatronic, Energy policy."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD - Material science and solid-state devices\n, Sheffield Hallam University, Sheffield, UK, 2017-2021.\nMSc (Research) – Microelectronics and Nanotechnology\n, De Montfort University, Leicester, UK, 2011-2014.\nBEng (Hons) – Electronic Engineering\n, De Montfort University, Leicester, UK, 2010-2011.\nHND – Electrical/Electronic Engineering (Communication)\n, EDEXCEL, UK, 2008-2010."
    }
  ],
